9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 935, L.D. 1426, “Resolve, to Expand
10 Child Assertive Community Treatment”
11 Amend the resolve in the emergency preamble in the 6th paragraph in the 2nd line
12 (page 1, line 13 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "2"
13 Amend the resolve by striking out all of section 1 and inserting the following:
14 'Sec. 1. Child assertive community treatment teams. Resolved: That, by
15 December 31, 2025, the Department of Health and Human Services shall issue a request
16 for applications for grants to establish pilot programs to develop 2 child assertive
17 community treatment teams to serve the Lewiston and Bangor geographic areas. The
18 request for applications must require the awardees of the grants to use workforce incentives
19 designed to attract, train and retain child assertive community treatment staff. The
20 department shall engage in a competitive process to determine the awardees. A single
21 entity may be awarded both grants. The term of the contracts may not exceed 2 years.'
22 Amend the resolve in section 2 in the last line (page 1, line 32 in L.D.) by inserting
23 after the following: "programs." the following: 'The joint standing committee is authorized
24 to report out legislation related to the report to the next regular or special session after the
25 report is received.'
26 Amend the resolve by striking out all of section 3 and inserting the following:
27 'Sec. 3. Appropriations and allocations. Resolved: That the following
28 appropriations and allocations are made.
29 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
